From e1024f6f71cca33bf5c41ab56f088209cee3070d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ryan Hankins <ryan.hankins@hpe.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 17:16:01 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] rdma: split mr[] into mr_data[], mr_ctrl_owned[],
 mr_ctrl[] views

In preparation for FI_MR_ENDPOINT support, the monolithic mr[] array
is replaced with three distinct fields:

  mr_data[0..num_rails-1]        owned fid_mr objects for data ep rails
  mr_ctrl_owned[0..num_ctrl_rails-1]  (empty until FI_MR_ENDPOINT support
                                        is added; reserved for ctrl ep rails)
  mr_ctrl[0..num_ctrl_rails-1]   non-owning raw-pointer view; always
                                  populated after registration

In non-endpoint-MR mode (the only mode supported at this stage), mr_ctrl[]
is aliased to mr_data[] entry-for-entry so that IO-path callers can always
use mr_ctrl[rail_id] without checking whether the field is populated.

Update all read sites to their final form:
  - data path (post_rdma_write, post_rdma_eager_send, post_eager_copy,
    alloc_rdma_read_req, write, post_flush_req): mr_data[rail_id]
  - ctrl path (send_ctrl_post, post_rdma_ctrl): mr_ctrl[rail_id]
  - prepare_send_connect_message: mr_ctrl[rail_id] iterated over
    num_control_rails (== num_rails in non-endpoint-MR mode)
  - post_rx_buffer: mr_data[rail_id] (will gain is_ctrl selection later)
  - get_mr_key: mr_data[0]

No behaviour change: in non-endpoint-MR mode mr_ctrl[] aliases mr_data[],
so every code path uses the same fid_mr as before.

Signed-off-by: Ryan Hankins <ryan.hankins@hpe.com>
---
 include/nccl_ofi_rdma.h | 37 +++++++++++++++++++---
 src/nccl_ofi_rdma.cpp   | 70 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++---------------
 2 files changed, 76 insertions(+), 31 deletions(-)

