From 671d0584aadeecb92cabd3b9bc5c0002d231f571 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ryan Hankins <ryan.hankins@hpe.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 17:19:16 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] rdma: thread endpoint pointer through reg_mr chain

Add an nccl_net_ofi_rdma_ep_t *ep parameter to:

  reg_mr_on_device(), reg_mr(), reg_internal_mr(), reg_internal_mr_dma_buf()

and forward it through every call site:

  - send_comm::regMr / recv_comm::regMr   pass the endpoint from this->ep
  - create_send_comm ctrl_mailbox reg     passes this (the send ep)
  - prepare_recv_comm ctrl_mailbox reg    passes l_comm_ep (the recv ep)
  - alloc_and_reg_flush_buff              passes nullptr (domain-owned)
  - freelist_regmr_host_fn                passes nullptr (no ep binding yet)

The ep pointer is not yet used inside reg_mr_on_device; that is the
subject of the next commit.  Callers that must not perform per-endpoint
binding (flush buffer, freelist registration) explicitly pass nullptr.

Signed-off-by: Ryan Hankins <ryan.hankins@hpe.com>
---
 include/nccl_ofi_rdma.h |  4 ++++
 src/nccl_ofi_rdma.cpp   | 50 ++++++++++++++++++++---------------------
 2 files changed, 28 insertions(+), 26 deletions(-)

