From a0a75fb9d977bec0ad9e9fa38e6fa1f5b06985a9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ryan Hankins <ryan.hankins@hpe.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Apr 2026 17:21:07 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] rdma: implement FI_MR_ENDPOINT bind/enable in
 reg_mr_on_device

When an endpoint pointer is supplied (ep != nullptr), reg_mr_on_device
now performs the fi_mr_bind + fi_mr_enable steps required by
FI_MR_ENDPOINT providers:

  - Data rails: each fid_mr is bound to the data ep rail and enabled.
  - Ctrl rails: a separate fid_mr is registered per ctrl ep rail, bound,
    and enabled; the owned handles are stored in mr_ctrl_owned[] and
    mr_ctrl[] is set to point into them.

A new private helper mr_bind_and_enable() encapsulates the bind+enable
sequence and produces uniform diagnostic messages.

In non-endpoint-MR mode (ep == nullptr) the function behaves exactly as
before: a single domain-level fid_mr per rail is registered without any
endpoint binding.

Additionally:
  - Advertise FI_MR_ENDPOINT in the libfabric hints so that providers
    that require it can negotiate the mode bit.
  - Remove the early-exit guard in nccl_net_ofi_rdma_init() that
    rejected endpoint_mr configurations with -ENOTSUP.
Signed-off-by: Ryan Hankins <ryan.hankins@hpe.com>
---
 include/nccl_ofi_rdma.h | 23 +++++++++++
 src/nccl_ofi_rdma.cpp   | 91 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++--------
 2 files changed, 97 insertions(+), 17 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/nccl_ofi_rdma.h b/include/nccl_ofi_rdma.h
